==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Typhoean
<hw>Ty*pho"e*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Typhoius</ets>, from <ets>Typhoeus</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to Typhoeus <pr>(t⟦isl⟧*f⟦omac⟧"⟦umac⟧s)</pr>, the
fabled giant of Greek mythology, having a hundred heads; resembling
Typhoeus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Sometimes incorrectly written and pronounced
<it>Ty-ph⟦oe⟧⟦bprime⟧an</it> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, or
<it>Ty-phe⟦bprime⟧an.</it></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Typhoid</ent>⟦br⟧
